## Outside this repo (referenced, never stamped)

- **`USER_NOTES`** (the engine profile): voice, signature, transparency line,
  recipient-language rule, LLM-ism ban, product mechanics. The biggest
  per-company artifact — read/edit via `cs rpc settings.update`, NEVER a repo file.
- **Secrets**: `EMAIL_PASSWORD`, `FIREBASE_WEB_API_KEY`, the real account uids
  (`CS_ACCOUNTS`), the SA key, `SMS_BUSINESS_ID` — in `~/.{{ company_slug }}-cs/.env` (see `.env.example`).
- **The kernel source** (`cs/`): not here — pinned in `requirements.txt`, installed into `.venv`.

## The generic skeleton (all from the kernel)

The body/brain split, the two campaign lifecycles, the send boundary, the
autonomy model and the safety NEVERs are kernel-owned and identical for every
clone — see the kernel charter (`cs-kernel` `CLAUDE.md`) and the design brief
`cs-kernel-manifest-separation.md`. This repo carries only: `manifest.toml`,
the rendered `.claude/` + `bin/` + docs, `company/*.md` prose, `campaigns/`
packs, and this clone's own `docs/projects/`.

